  "description": "Hey folks! I hope everyone\u0026rsquo;s week has been going well. I\u0026rsquo;ve enjoyed the little conversations some of us have been having through the week.\nToday I\u0026rsquo;d like to announce a small little project I\u0026rsquo;m working on: HashUp.\nI\u0026rsquo;ve always been dissastisfied with the physical act of writing: with pen and paper it\u0026rsquo;s slow and requires a fair amount of concentration to write smoothly, and with computers\u0026hellip; well, there\u0026rsquo;s What-you-see-is-what-you-get style editors like #Word, which I dislike: I\u0026rsquo;m not trying to typeset a document to be printed, I\u0026rsquo;m trying to write! Unfortunately, most non-WYSIWYG editors and formatting languages like #Markdown are similar in the same fundamental way: they exist to facilitate visual formatting, not help an author encode semantic meaning.\n",
  "name": "HashUp semantic plaintext markup",
